modules.description: Provides functions for storing and retrieving key/value pairs, with support for transactional operations and session management. Works with persistent data structures and database backends such as PostgreSQL and SQLite. Used to manage user sessions and application state in web applications built with Eliom/Ocsigen.

Loads and parses PostgreSQL connection settings from XML configuration files, supporting both TCP and UNIX domain socket connections. Processes attributes such as host, port, user, password, and connection pool size. Used to initialize database connections in Ocsigen Server applications with predefined settings.
